{"block1":"<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Every year, millions of men and women are affected by hemorrhoids. In fact, nearly half of all adults have experienced them by the time they are fifty. Hemorrhoids can be uncomfortable. A person may bleed, itch, or be in pain when suffering from them. However, effective treatment options are available. Many treatments are safe for use at home, and there are also adjustments you can make to your lifestyle that can help prevent them. This article reviews several such options for treating your hemorrhoids.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"\/images\/man-drinking-a-glass-of-water.jpg\" class=\"img_left \" alt=\"man drinking a glass of water\" style=\"float: left; padding: 8px; padding-left: 0;\" \/><\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Some hemorrhoids can cause extreme pain. Ice can be helpful in&nbsp;reducing swelling and decreasing pain. For even more relief, you can replace ice with warmer compresses and keep switching back and forth between the two. Soaking in a warm tub, and then applying an ice pack will reduce swelling and pain related to hemorrhoids, and help you be more comfortable.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Drink eight glasses of water a day. Few tips are as effective and affordable as this one! A major cause of hemorrhoids is constipation, and this can be alleviated by increasing your water consumption.&nbsp;It also helps to thoroughly clean out your system. Try to drink 10 glasses of water every day.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"\/images\/various-laxatives-isolated-on-white.jpg\" class=\"img_right \" alt=\"various laxatives isolated on white\" style=\"float: right; padding: 8px; padding-right: 0;\" \/><\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">To <a href=\"advice-on-how-to-lessen-the-impact-hemorroids-have-on-your-life\"  >deal with hemorrhoids effectively<\/a>, don&#39;t sit on the toilet too long while you wait to defecate. This position can put excess strain on hemorrhoids, causing extra pain and irritation, and slower healing. Wait for your natural urge prior to going to the toilet.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Laxatives only help you move your bowels once, so do not depend upon them to alleviate your problems with hemorrhoids. You may get through the next couple of days with ease after taking laxatives, but you need to take other measures to actually&nbsp;<a href=\"http:\/\/hemorrhoidreport.net\/hemorrhoid-information\/cures-for-hemorrhoids\/\"  >cure your hemorrhoids<\/a>.<\/p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">So there is hope for hemorrhoids sufferers - you don&#39;t have to put up with them. Most of the time, home treatments work and surgery is pretty rare. Now that you understand how hemorrhoids are treated and caused, hopefully, you can get your case under control.<\/p>\r\n"}